Package org.billtorcaso.Stopwatch

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Stopwatch
    The Stopwatch interface records an sequence of named moments, with nanosecond intervals and minimal run-time overhead.
    Stopwatch.Moment
    The Moment interface represents an immutable "moment in time", consisting of a long integer value and a String title.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MomentImpl
    This class represents a "moment", with a long integer value like that returned from System.nanoTime() and a String title.
    StopwatchFactory
    This class is the factory for Stopwatch objects.
    StopwatchImpl
    This class implements the Stopwatch interface.
    StopwatchInstance
    This class provides class-static services for a shareable singleton Stopwatch object.
    StopwatchNoOpImpl
    This class implements the Stopwatch interface but does nothing, so as to minimize the overhead of embedded calls on a Stopwatch.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Stopwatch.IntervalReportType
    This enum represents the various interpretations of when.
    Stopwatch.TimeElapsedType
    This enum represents the various measures of elapsed time.
